headline: Gen Z Can't Rely On 'I Can Work Hard,' Says Jamie Dimon — AI Is Rewriting The Rules For $62K Jobs And First-Time Home Buyers
summary: The belief that effort alone can secure a stable future is fading as artificial intelligence reshapes how Gen Z enters work and housing markets. That shift is already visible, JPMorgan Chase (NYSE:JPM) CEO Jamie Dimon told CNN recently. He said past generations could build stable lives through consistent labor, even without advanced education, but today's workers face different conditions, from rising living costs to rapid changes driven by technology.
